text: Noyers-Bocage is a former commune. It is found in the Normandy region in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Noyers-Missy,Arrêté préfectoral 9 December 2015 which became part of the new commune Val d'Arry on 1 January 2017. == References == Category:Former communes in Calvados
title: Noyers-Bocage
